<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A more mature server would be great.  However, keep in mind that you may eliminate new people rather than the annoying people.  For example, I have only been playing for a month and a half, and have only recently found out what a train is.  No one really explains all this stuff to us when we begin.  For example, some higher level players kill things and leave the corpses for the lower level ppl to loot so that they can get some money.  On the same token, others just leave the bodies strewn across the acreage intending to pick it up later.  How is a newbie supposed to know which it is?  Especially one trying to role-play, and not willing to "shout" every two seconds?  Also, its hard to figure out how to make socials and run while typing etc, so I think we need to find out why someone is doing something before we chalk them up to being a bad gamer.  Sometimes they just don`t know better.  I would like to see some people more dedicated to role-playing.  Myself and another druid zoned into someones train of kobald`s the other week and his friend (complete strangers btw) gave us heck for not healing him....there were many things wrong with that.  First of all, when being attacted yourself, spells get interrupted, secondly, its extremely hard to mouse click on a dwarf in a sea of kobalds.  Thirdly, it eliminated the idea that we may have roleplaying issues with healing strangers....Ie/ what if I decide to follow the idea that dark elves are evil?  Should i be expected to heal them still?  I don`t think so...  I had to wonder why this person assumed all of this.  That is the type of person I would like to avoid in the future.<BR>&lt;Them and the ones who occasionally try to get me to go behind a tree with them&gt;  I would like a server to eliminate these types.<BR>Cressida (Keepers of the Fiery Myste) lvl 14 druid. 
</FONT>
